<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=5571&amp;p=50669#p50669</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=5571&amp;p=50669#p50669"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Average size for music engine]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=5571&amp;p=50669#p50669"><![CDATA[
Use the SVN build of FCEUX, and use the Code/Data Logger on all the songs in an NSF. You can use this to get an accurate readout of your desired data this way(Bytes Logged As Code), though, this only accounts for code actually used, not likely the error-recovery code, or branches not used due to no sound effect usage.<br /><br />I suggest FCEUX because it works with the speedup button. If you're willing to wait, then you can use my copy of FCEUXDSP, which is pre-built and on my page.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=229">ugetab</a> — Wed Sep 16, 2009 9:28 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
