<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=5571&amp;p=50667#p50667</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=5571&amp;p=50667#p50667"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Average size for music engine]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=5571&amp;p=50667#p50667"><![CDATA[
The driver I use im my current game is fairly small, about 650 bytes total (including all code to run sound, start and stop music&amp;SFX, lockup tables, but no music/SFX data itself).<br />As my game is 32kb so I don't want to waste a lot of music. It's possible to come with a very small driver, that only fetches data and write stuff to registers, and then come with a customizable effect system, so that you waste as much size as you want for the extra effect (like vibratoes, software pitch slides, arpeggio, etc...)<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=38">Bregalad</a> — Wed Sep 16, 2009 8:42 am</p><hr />
