<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=5571&amp;p=50660#p50660</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=5571&amp;p=50660#p50660"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Average size for music engine]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=5571&amp;p=50660#p50660"><![CDATA[
The Guardian Legend's sound engine is 2,439 bytes:<br /><br /><strong>Code</strong> takes up 1782 bytes.<br /><br /><strong>LUTs </strong>take up 657 bytes.  These tables include all the volume envelopes and pitch envelopes, since The Guardian Legend doesn't use an instrument system.  If you don't want to count these, LUTs only take up 295 bytes (for a sound engine total of 2077).<br /><br />That's the only sound engine I know about in great detail, so I can't comment on averages.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=3632">MetalSlime</a> — Tue Sep 15, 2009 11:14 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
